> Gary,
>
> Don't we need the springy play in those assemblies? I carry spares anyway.
>

One of the old  tricks was to shim stock rocker assemblies, getting rid of
the wavy washers for engine's revving higher than normal. Wire the clips so
they can't pop off as well.

I've done this with excellent results. Just make sure you shim them right so
the rocker still rotates the valve.

